# Path pointers to team-shared sensitive pattern files.
# One absolute path per line. Lines starting with # are comments.
# On macOS/Linux, prefer symlinks in ~/.claude/business-patterns.d/ — they auto-update via git pull.
# On Windows or when symlinks aren't practical, use this file instead.
#
# Copy this to `business-patterns.paths` (no .example suffix) in your local
# clone and add the paths you want the scanner to include. The real file is
# git-ignored; this .example template is committed.

# Example (adapt to your environment):
# $HOME/.claude/local/team-patterns/your-org.txt
